A new study of high-growth firms in Greater Washington, D.C., highlights the role of community in a thriving economy.



The past decade or so has seen the rise of a new formula for urban economic growth and development. While having a solid business climate that attracts companies and jobs remains important, it is also necessary to cultivate a vibrant, exciting community with a wide diversity of talent.
